                  <additions>
                     <label>Table of Contents:</label>
                     Folios <locus from="1b" to="4a">1b to 4a</locus> list the events described within this volume.
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           Former owner <persName role="fmo ins" key="person_44733962" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44733962/">Sir Gore Ouseley</persName> inscribed his bookplate on the <locus from="Inner_back_cover" to="Inner_back_cover">left pastedown</locus> <q xml:lang="en">To my friend Colonel Fitz Clarence</q>.
                        </item>
                     </list>
                     <label>Bookplates and Pasted Remnants:</label>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           The <locus from="ib" to="ib">right flyleaf b side (f. ib)</locus> bears the remnants of printed descriptions of the work, likely entries from the catalogue of oriental manuscripts <orgName>Royal Asiatic Society</orgName> by former owner <persName type="standard" role="fmo"
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/56966054/" key="person_56966054">William Hook
                              Morley</persName> that describes the contents of this volume, given identifiable portions from the same location in <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7312"><idno>Persian MS 806</idno></ref>
                        </item>
                        <item><locus from="Inner_front_cover" to="Inner_front_cover">Right pastedown</locus>: <persName role="fmo ins" key="person_44733962" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44733962/">Sir Gore Ouseley</persName>.</item>
                        <item>The <locus from="Inner_back_cover" to="Inner_back_cover">Left pastedown</locus>: 
